# Keep Rust source files as LF in the repository, regardless of a contributor's
# core.autocrlf setting. This prevents Windows checkouts from committing CRLF and
# producing whole-file diffs / merge conflicts in the source the team edits.
#
# Deliberately scoped to *.rs: the rest of the repo (docs, workflows, etc.) was
# historically committed with CRLF, and forcing eol=lf on it would trigger a
# mass renormalization unrelated to any current change.
*.rs    text eol=lf
